Task: map every use of the `calllog.Counter` type across sofia-ctx/sofia
(frozen at BASE_SHA). Usage comprehension across ~20 files — no edits expected.

Reference facts (frozen, verified by reading the real files at BASE_SHA via
`sf refs Counter --max 100`): 1 definition + 31 uses = 32 references total.

1) Uniform pattern (holds for 22 of the call sites):
   `cw := &calllog.Counter{W: w}` — created near the TOP of a feature's logic
   entry function `func Run(opts ..., w io.Writer) error` (or a RunX sibling),
   right after the calllog span is opened, wiring the Counter's `W` field to
   that function's `w io.Writer` output parameter so emitted bytes/tokens are
   metered. The 22 uniform sites (file → enclosing func):
     internal/cc/bash.go:179 runBash
     internal/cc/candidates.go:241 runCandidates
     internal/cc/ls.go:99 runLs
